                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">703.94/13884: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-15T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 15, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 15—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1471. Mandel, Minister of Colonies, said to me today that 2 days ago the Japanese
                    had occupied a small island about 25 miles from the coast of the Island of
                    Hainan and had bombarded Hainan. He expressed the opinion that this action of
                    the Japanese Navy was not unrelated to the extreme tension which had arisen in
                    Europe over the Czechoslovak crisis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
